# SajiloYatra Database Management System

## Overview
SajiloYatra is a Bus Transportation Database Management System developed using Oracle SQL. The project manages passengers, bookings, buses, routes, tickets, payments, and staff operations.

This project demonstrates database design concepts including:
- ERD Design
- Database Normalization
- Primary and Foreign Keys
- SQL Queries
- Data Manipulation
- Transaction Queries

---

## Technologies Used
- Oracle SQL
- Draw.io
- Relational Database Design
- SQL Queries
- Database Normalization (1NF, 2NF, 3NF)

---

## Features
- Passenger Management
- Bus and Route Management
- Ticket Booking System
- Payment Tracking
- Staff Assignment System
- Revenue Analysis
- Trip Scheduling

---

## Database Concepts Used
- ERD Design
- Primary & Foreign Keys
- Constraints
- Joins
- Aggregate Functions
- Group By Queries
- Nested Queries
- Transaction Queries

---

## Sample Queries
- Total revenue generated per route
- Top passengers with most bookings
- Trips operating below 50% capacity
- Latest departing trip
- Payment status tracking

